<br>
If you think Healers are frustratingly non-offensive, wait til you play a Bard. Non-offensive with no defensive capabilities all in one class. Whee! I doubt instant CC spells will bring back most of the bards who have moved on to other classes. Thus PvE in Hibernia will stick to AE groups and RvR will rely on root.<br>
<br>
In contrast, Midgard gets Insta-Mez from Skalds every 20 seconds and Insta-Mez, Insta-Stun (single and AE versions) from the Healer... not to mention Insta-heals and chain armor.<br>
<br>
Clerics have a instant point blank mez. Minstrels have the instant stun and mez while you dance around mez. Sorcerors have AE mez.<br>
<br>
Basically, for crowd control, Hibernia was in trouble.<br>
<br>
As for Druids... there was no escape. If a druid is in a bad situation, they die--no option to escape because they had no spells they could cast to get away. Now they have a chance. Mind you, while rooted, you can still shoot em with arrows or spells or throwing weapons, unlike mez and stun. Heck, if the druid doesn't move away you can still kill them.<br>
<br>
So Hibernia still has the weakest crowd control, and these instas were a very minor addition. A Healer is still more dangerous than a Bard. Insta-root is nice... but I can still kill someone while rooted, especially with my spell variance fixed.<br>
<br>
<i>And nerfs just plain suck. If I was a cleric I would be way pissed off, if the nerf is alot.</i><br>
<br>
Yeah, nerfs suck... but sometimes there's only one good way to control power inflation. Clerics had the nuking power of a wizard, decent heals, and decent buffs with chain armor thrown in. What options were there? Increase the spell damage of the Wizard, Eldritch and Runemaster and give Druids and Shaman massive nuking power?<br>
<br>
 <p><p style="text-align: right; font-size: 80%; font-family: Verdana">Jalena! Nightshade of Percival<br><i>Danger calls; it intoxicates. Beyond the walls real excitement waits.<br>Adreneline rush--dance along the ledge. Forbidden touch--kiss the razor's edge.</i></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=collainmacbain>Collain MacBain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 9:23:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3526.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1.51D Coming to Pendragon</span><hr size=1> As a shade I am glad they fixed the variance on my shout, which was long overdue. <br>
<br>
